                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="11403" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sun, 31 Oct 2004 21:04:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t reproduce this; I&apos;ve even added special test case to HibernateTransactionManagerTests. Do you have a minimal test case that reproduces your failure, or did you just suspect that this &lt;b&gt;might&lt;/b&gt; fail in the scenario you described?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;HibernateTransactionManager calls SessionHolder.clear() in its doCleanupAfterCompletion implementation, which resets the transactional state of the SessionHolder - including the rollbackOnly flag.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Of course, this is just relevant with OpenSessionInViewFilter in the first place, as the SessionHolder is discarded after transaction completion else - i.e. its state is irrelevant, because it&apos;s not gonna be used anymore.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11407" author="s.meyer" created="Mon, 1 Nov 2004 03:24:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In my specific case I use HibernateTransactionInterceptor to create a session when performing jobs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The method SessionHolder.clear() does not exist in my version of Spring (1.0.2). Also I have seen (debugging) that the SessionHolder instance is reused for a new transaction.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11409" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 1 Nov 2004 04:03:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, I see - I didn&apos;t notice that you were reporting this against 1.0.2. Thanks for the clarification. This has already been fixed since 1.1 RC1, so I recommend to upgrade to the 1.1 codebase. 1.1.2 is gonna be released tomorrow, so you might want to go straight for 1.1.2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
